# Force LF line endings for shell scripts and Python files even when checked
# out on Windows. Without this, Git on Windows converts LF → CRLF on checkout
# (the default `core.autocrlf=true`), and a subsequent `git pull` on a Linux
# host installs scripts whose shebang ends in \r — bash then fails to find
# the interpreter (`/usr/bin/env bash\r` does not exist) and cron just sees
# `command not found`. We had a real outage caused by this on 2026-05-24.
#
# `text eol=lf` tells Git to:
#   - treat the file as text (allow normalisation)
#   - always write LF in the working tree, on every platform
#
# Applies retroactively after `git add --renormalize .` is run once.

*.sh        text eol=lf
*.py        text eol=lf
*.env.example text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf

# Migrations and yaml: also force LF (postgres / docker tooling chokes on CRLF).
*.sql       text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.toml      text eol=lf

